================================================================================
                          QR READER FOR ANDROID
================================================================================

QR Reader for Android is an appplication for the Android platform. This 
application serves for the detection of the QR codes in the real-time camera 
preview and decoding of the QR codes on demand.

Minimum API for running the application: 9
Note: This application uses JNI and natively built Barcodes Library.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                          BUILDING THE APPLICATION

REQUIREMENTS:

1) Have an installed Android SDK.
2) Have an installed Android NDK and defined directory with ndk-build script 
   in the PATH.
3) Have generated file with the source files of the Barcodes Library inside
   library project directory (src_list.TXT). That can be done by invoking
   the GNU Make tool inside the project directory of the Barcodes Library:
       make gen-srclist
   
WAY 1) Use automatic build with the Eclipse and AVD: 
  - See: http://developer.android.com/guide/developing/projects/projects-eclipse.html

WAY 2) Use command line driven build: 
  - See: http://developer.android.com/guide/developing/projects/projects-cmdline.html
  - Do not forget run ndk-build before.

